    <bioghist>
<head> Biographical Information </head>
<p>George Smith Cook was born in Connecticut in 1819 and entered the photography business
      in New Orleans, Louisiana. He settled in Charleston, South Carolina, in 1849 with his first
      wife Elizabeth Smith Francisco and children, Francisca and George LaGrange. Cook married
      Elizabeth's niece Lavinia Elizabeth Pratt in 1866 after the death of Elizabeth in 1864. The
      couple had two children, Huestis Pratt and Lavinia Elizabeth. He moved in 1880 to Richmond,
      Virginia, where he continued as a photographer until his death in 1902. Huestis Pratt Cook was
      born in Charleston, South Carolina, in 1868. He moved to Richmond, Virginia, in 1880 with his
      family and entered the photography business. He married Mary Manning Latimer in 1913. The
      couple had two children, Susan Maxcy and Huestis Pratt, Jr. Huestis Cook died in 1951. Both
      George and Huestis Cook are buried in Hollywood Cemetery in Richmond, Va. </p></bioghist>

    <scopecontent>
<head> Scope and Content </head>
<p>The papers of George Cook include account books, business correspondence, receipts
      and various printed matter. The papers of Huestis Cook include both personal and business
      correspondence, notes and lists related to the photography business, publications, and printed
      matter containing Cook images. </p></scopecontent>

